A desperate search is on to find a student nurse who has been missing for more than three weeks. Police say they are ‘extremely concerned’ for the welfare of Owami Davies, 24, who left her family home on July 4. Owami, from Grays, Essex, was last seen at 12.03am on Derby Road in West Croydon on July 7. Officers said she was in a ‘vulnerable state’ at the time and are urging residents in West Croydon to look in their sheds and outbuildings and report anything ‘out of the ordinary’. Det Con Marie Spear said: ‘Owami’s family have not heard from her for more than three weeks and she has not turned up to work. ‘We are currently treating this as a missing person investigation. ‘Owami was in a vulnerable state when she was last seen and we need the public’s help in piecing together her movements on the night she went missing. ‘I would urge anyone who has seen her, or knows where she is, to contact police immediately. ‘I’d also ask people in the West Croydon area to check their sheds and outbuildings and report anything suspicious or out of the ordinary.’ Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.